  <scopecontent id="aspace_2048f8f24c94cdbfd824821a0c850946">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Exchange problems between Cornell and other universities, and landscape problems set by Bryant Fleming and Eugene D. Montillon; survey data and planting plans, 1908-1921; student projects, 1913-1931; student work for the American Academy in Rome by Edward Lawson, R. E. Griswold, and others; files on New York State institutions used as study data, 1898-1933; plans and measured drawings of historic estates by E. Gorton Davis, 1914-1929.</p>  </scopecontent>
